LEGS. Tibia and metatarsus I as shown in Fig. 132 . Scopula (thinner than in other congeners except for
R. micropa
): distal on metatarsi I–II, entire on tarsus I; divided by setae on tarsus II; only few scopuliform hairs on tarsi III–IV. Trichobothria: 2 rows of 10–11 each on tibiae, 11–13 on metatarsi, 11–14 on tarsi, 8–9 on cymbium. Paired claws: inner and outer margins with 7–8 teeth each on tarsi I–II, with 6–7 teeth each on tarsi III–IV.

SPERMATHECAE. Moderately long and wide, with receptacles close set to each other (
Fig. 202
).
